Incident.Summary: Female complainant advised she was raped by her friend's boyfriend after a night of group sex activities.

IncidentSuppNarrative.NarrativeText:
On April 27, 2023 at approximately 1543 hours, I, S/Tpr. Wilkins was dispatched to respond to the Maryland State Police Salisbury Barrack to meet with a female complainant in the lobby regarding a rape. 

     Upon my arrival, I met with a female identified as Courtney Ann Torlish W/F 09/06/1981. Due to the severity and sensitive nature of the accusations, I asked Torlish if she would be willing to agree to speak in private in the Salisbury Barrack recorded interview room, she agreed. I directed Torlish to the room, and began to speak with her. 

    Torlish explained the following to me regarding the incident: 
  • The night prior (April 26, 2013), Torlish, a friend identified as Marissa O'Donnell, and O'Donnell's boyfriend only identified as "Corey" all met up and mutually agreed to engage in a three-way sexual encounter. 
  • Torlish advised she was picked up, and all three went back to the address where the crime occurred which was 800 Miami Avenue, Salisbury, Wicomico County, Maryland 
  • Torlish advised they arrived at the address at around 12 o'clock midnight. 
  • Torlish stated once there, "Corey" provided a hand rolled marijuana cigarette, that she was believed laced with another drug (molly), based off "Corey's" statements 
  • Torlish stated the three parties then became mutually engaged in consensual sex. 
  • Torlish stated the consensual sexual activities lasted until about 0800 hours on today's date (April 27, 2023)
  • Torlish stated O'Donnell had to be to work at the pawn shop in Delmar, Delaware at around 0930 hours. 
  • Torlish stated "Corey" left to take O'Donnell to work, then returned to the 800 Miami Avenue address. 
  • Torlish stated due to the exhaustive nature of the previous nights activities, she was attempting to sleep while "Corey" took O'Donnell to work. 
  • Torlish stated once "Corey" arrived back at the address after dropping O'Donnell off, he walked back into the house, into the bedroom where she was sleeping. 
  • Torlish stated "Corey" was butt-naked, and woke her up. "Corey" then stated, "...come on, we're gonna have sex." 
  • Torlish stated she told "Corey", "...no, I'm not going to disrespect her she's not here," explaining she did not want to have sex with "Corey" without O'Donnell there, as O'Donnell and "Corey" were currently in a relationship. 
  • Torlish stated "Corey" was persistent, ultimately resulting in him forcibly flipping her onto her stomach, taking her pajama pants off, and then engaging in vaginal intercourse with her. 
  • Torlish stated she was fearful for what "Corey" would do if she tried to fend him off. 
  • Torlish stated as "Corey" was raping her, he stated, "...I'm going to get you pregnant." 
  • Torlish stated she was crying as the incident occurred. 
  • Torlish advised she was wearing a bra, red t-shirt, black sweat shirt, and pajama pants (which were removed). 
  • Torlish stated she could physically feel "Corey" ejaculate, and finished having sex with her. 
  • Torlish stated she then got re-dressed, and layed in the bed for a period of time before she asked "Corey" to drive her home, to which "Corey" agreed.
  • Torlish stated the clothing she wore were still at her residence in Laurel, and she did not wash them yet. 
    I asked Torlish to describe any details from the location of the room or anything in the room. Torlish stated it was a bedroom in the residence. Torlish stated there were no pillow cases, the sheets were white with a floral design, and there was a heat lamp in the room where "Corey" was growing suspected illegal crops. Torlish stated once she arrived home, she immediately got a shower. After getting out of the shower she spoke with her roommate, and told her what happened. Torlish stated her roommate then told her she was bringing her to the police to report the incident. 

     I asked Torlish if she could provide any other information on the suspect. She then showed me a Facebook profile on her cell phone of a subject with the name "Damone FREEZER Wilson". Information listened on the subject further described him as from Dover, Delaware, from Star Hill Village, DE. I asked Torlish if she believed this was the suspect, and she stated she was pretty sure that was him. Torlish further described the suspect as a black male, between 5'-5'05" and 150 lbs.

     Due to the complexity of the investigation and the allegations being made by Torlish, a request for investigators from the Maryland State Police-Criminal Enforcement Division was made to respond. Sgt. Watkins, Cpl. Hager, and S/Tpr Dick all with MSP-CED all responded to assist with the investigation. 

     At this time, I request this case remain open, forwarded to CED. 

     All above events did occur in Wicomico County, Maryland.
